\begin_layout Section*
Question 2
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The chosen firm is PepsiCo Inc.
 (PEP)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
a.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Total debt is 
\begin_inset Formula $44.57B$
\end_inset

, the equity is 
\begin_inset Formula $13.6B$
\end_inset

.
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{D}{E+D}=\frac{44.57}{13.6+44.57}=0.766
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{E}{E+D}=\frac{13.6}{13.6+44.57}=0.234
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Given YTM of 20 year bonds 
\begin_inset Formula $1.61\%$
\end_inset

, the firm's beta is 0.57 and 
\begin_inset Formula $r_{E}=5.05\%$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The interest expense is 
\begin_inset Formula $\$1.233B$
\end_inset

 and the net debt is 
\begin_inset Formula $\$26.559B$
\end_inset

, thus the average interest paid is:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{1.233}{26.559}=4.643\%
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
WACC=\frac{D}{E+D}r_{D}+\frac{E}{E+D}r_{E}=0.766\cdot4.643\%+0.234\cdot5.05\%=4.738\%
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
b.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The implied tax rate is the tax provision, divided by the pretax income:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{1859}{8756}=21.23\%
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The interest tax shield is:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
r_{D}\cdot D\cdot t_{c}=\$1.223B\cdot21.23\%=\$0.26B
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Section*
Question 3
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
a.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The annual tax shield is:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
r_{D}\cdot D\cdot t_{c}=6\%\cdot\$100M\cdot40\%=\$2.4M
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
b.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The total present value of the tax shield is:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
t_{c}\cdot D=\$100M\cdot40\%=\$40M
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
c.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The value of the firm is the sum of its equity and debt, and the present
 value of the tax shield:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\$300M+\$100M+\$40M=\$440M
\]

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
d.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The annual tax shield is:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
r_{D}\cdot D\cdot t_{c}=5\%\cdot\$100M\cdot40\%=\$2M
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The total present value of the tax shield and the value of the firm don't
 change, as they do not depend on 
\begin_inset Formula $r_{D}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

